"John Miller voluntarily says, that on Saturday morning last he met Joseph Durden, and said to him he knew where there were two bundles of things under some hay - Joseph Durden afterwards said he knew a young man who would buy them if they could agree to price;
John Franco
then came to the Jolly Ostler; Durden said he would show him the things, which he did, andhe asked 3l. for them, and Franco offered 30s. - he then took the things back to the place where they were found - Durden fetched one of the bundles along with him, and they took them to his father's stables; he said he should leave it all to Durden to sell the bundles for him; there were forty-eight pairs of gaiters when he had them - five pairs were missing.
